history.content:
yes

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

On another note, imo I wouldn't advise CS C8 for someone who has taken 61A. The coding side will be incredibly easy after taking 61A (other than having to memorize some tiny quirks for the Tables framework that is used for the class). For the prob/stats side, you may benefit more from taking stat 134/140/135 or ee 126 if you're interested in doing DS/AI/ML since you would anyways have to take those courses for that field. That being said, if you're looking for an easy class, CS C8 will def be an easy A if you've done 61A.
